  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is difficult to predict which patients with acute small bowel obstruction require
      operative intervention and which ones can be handled conservatively. Similarly, strangulation
      remains difficult decision. The rationale for this observative study is to collect
      prospective cohort of patients with small bowel obstruction to create scoring system to
      predict early 1) small bowel obstruction resistant to conservative therapy, 2) strangulation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
